{"id":445,"date":"2020-08-23T17:17:40","date_gmt":"2020-08-23T17:17:40","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/?p=445"},"modified":"2020-08-23T17:17:43","modified_gmt":"2020-08-23T17:17:43","slug":"an-evening-at-saturday-night-market","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/an-evening-at-saturday-night-market\/","title":{"rendered":"An Evening at Saturday Night Market"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Goa, when you hear the word, the first things that come to mind are pristine beaches and marvellous Portuguese architecture. Tourists both domestic and international come down to Goa for spending their vacation break to enjoy the natural beauty of the surreal landscapes and the relaxing ambience it creates. Britishers, Russians and other tourists from European countries form the majority of the foreign crowd.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Goa has got into the limelight for being the most sought-after tourist destination. Most of it because of the beaches, the architecture and the nightlife. Now there is one reason added to the list of what one should do in Goa. It is Goa\u2019s famous Saturday night market. The night market is famous among the tourist both domestic and international who visits it every time they are in Goa to check out what it has to offer.<br> If you are new to Goa, let us help you to know more about this amazing place.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>How to get to the Saturday Night Market<br><\/strong>Located in Arpora, the Saturday night market is 18 kilometers from Panjim, the capital city of Goa. One can get city buses from the Panjim bus terminal or one can hire a rickshaw or rent a car from the car rental agencies. If you are already in coastal belt areas such as Calangute or Baga, then reaching the spot is less time-consuming.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What you can find at Saturday Night Market<br><\/strong>The Saturday night market offers a wide experience to its guests. The total area is divided into 3 regions. The lower area has all the stalls offering clothes, shoes, leather bags and goods. Few vendors sell silver jewelery and other handicraft products to those who are inclined towards art and body accessories. One can find nice Kashmiri pashmina shawls to keep them warm in the cold chilly night.<br>The mid-area is for all the foodie enthusiasts. You will find stalls offering cuisines from Italian, Indian to Mexican &amp; Greek. Also there are a few bars offering beer, wine, local drinks &amp; cocktails. Savour on some rolled sushi and dimsums while enjoying nice live music by local &amp; international musical artists and groups.<br>The top area has some stalls lined up showcasing some international clothing brands along with a house bar in the top right offering nice delicious cocktails to sip on along with nice live DJ sets grooving you on some hit numbers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What are the timings to visit this place?<br><\/strong>Tourists flock this spot around December and it goes till March. One can find the maximum crowd during this time. The place starts gearing up with the crowd at around 6pm and is active even after 12 am.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The place is dolled up with nice lighting and good music which makes it a really good place to spend an evening when you are in Goa. Don&#8217;t forget to experience a night of good food, music and amazing stalls that will surely be memorable for a long time.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Goa, when you hear the word, the first things that come to mind are pristine beaches and marvellous Portuguese architecture. Tourists both domestic and international come down to Goa for spending their vacation break to enjoy the natural beauty of the surreal landscapes and the relaxing ambience it creates. Britishers, Russians and other tourists from [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":449,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories